verbose_text: In macrophages, a recent study showed that the CD14 / TLR4 (a Toll like receptor 4)/MD-2 complex interacts with mmLDL, inducing cytoskeletal rearrangements and the secretion of macrophage inflammatory protein-2, MCP-1, tumor necrosis factor-alpha (TNF-alpha) and interleukin-6 via ROS generation from spleen tyrosine kinase / Nox2 signaling.
